# d169e6dc786b4175be2e19e6822317a6
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:40
msgid ""
"The URL data structure is a parsed version of a standard internet URL. "
"The Traffic Server URL API provides access to URL data stored in marshal "
"buffers. The URL functions can create, copy, retrieve or delete entire "
"URLs, and retrieve or modify parts of URLs, such as their host, port or "
"scheme information."
msgstr ""

# 17315a3e81bd469db4460495f8381cb7
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:46
msgid ""
":func:`TSUrlCreate` creates a new URL within the marshal buffer "
":arg:`bufp`. Release the resulting handle with a call to "
":func:`TSHandleMLocRelease`."
msgstr ""

# a69718b83f5c48e5819a108f34c3754a
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:50
msgid ""
":func:`TSUrlClone` copies the contents of the URL at location "
":arg:`src_url` within the marshal buffer :arg:`src_bufp` to a location "
"within the marshal buffer :arg:`dest_bufp`. Release the returned handle "
"with a call to :func:`TSHandleMLocRelease`."
msgstr ""

# 2d3f1d1e2d344f5580ba46a769134e99
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:55
msgid ""
":func:`TSUrlCopy` copies the contents of the URL at location "
":arg:`src_url` within the marshal buffer :arg:`src_bufp` to the location "
":arg:`dest_url` within the marshal buffer dest_bufp. :func:`TSUrlCopy` "
"works correctly even if :arg:`src_bufp` and :arg:`dest_bufp` point to "
"different marshal buffers. It is important for the destination URL (its "
"marshal buffer and :type:`TSMLoc`) to have been created before copying "
"into it."
msgstr ""

# f2b6524ff1b3422bb6a91bd37e073689
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:62
msgid ""
":func:`TSUrlParse` parses a URL. The :arg:`start` pointer is both an "
"input and an output parameter and marks the start of the URL to be "
"parsed. After a successful parse, the :arg:`start` pointer equals the "
":arg:`end` pointer. The :arg:`end` pointer must be one byte after the "
"last character you want to parse. The URL parsing routine assumes that "
"everything between :arg:`start` and :arg:`end` is part of the URL. It is "
"up to higher level parsing routines, such as :func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq`, "
"to determine the actual end of the URL."
msgstr ""

# b781c141b4094aa69d2af2b61e452926
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:72
msgid "Return Values"
msgstr ""

# b6c6685ac28b49c6b349dcdc4dd336ee
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSUrlCreate.en.rst:74
msgid ""
"The :func:`TSUrlParse` function returns a :type:`TSParseResult`, where "
":data:`TS_PARSE_ERROR` indicates an error. Success is indicated by one of"
" :data:`TS_PARSE_DONE`, :data:`TS_PARSE_OK` or :data:`TS_PARSE_CONT`. The"
" other APIs all return a :type:`TSReturnCode`, indicating success "
"(:data:`TS_SUCCESS`) or failure (:data:`TS_ERROR`) of the operation."
msgstr ""

